did.abstract: Newspaper clippings and records created by the Whitman College Communications Office

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: President Clemen created the Office of Public Relations in 1935 to coordinate college publicity and student recruiting activities. He appointed Victor Shawe as the first Director of Public Relations. The current Whitman College Communications Office, part of the Development and College Relations group, is responsible for promoting Whitman College as well as communicating the goals and accomplishments of the college people and departments. The Communications Office publishes Whitman Magazine and The Fountain campus newsletter and manages the college Web site, media relations, and other communications services.

scopecontent.p: The collection consists of records relating to the Whitman College Communications Office. The collection is divided into six series: News Service, Public Events, Communications Office records, newspaper clippings, and photographic material

accessrestrict.p: Some of the more current records may be restricted.

userestrict.p: Researchers are responsible for using in accordance with 17 U.S.C. for copyright not held by Whitman College.

prefercite.p: Whitman College Communications Office Records, Whitman College and Northwest Archives.

acqinfo.p: Materials are regularly transferred to the Whitman College and Northwest Archives.
